<strong>Elevation gain:</strong> 405 m
</div>

<p>This Okunikko favorite traces the Yukawa River upstream from the twin cascades of Ryūzu Falls to the thunderous curtain of Yudaki. Wooden boardwalks, riverside paths, and forest staircases keep you close to the water the entire way, with seasonal views of azaleas in spring and brilliant larch colors in autumn.</p>

<p>The middle section passes Lake Chuzenji&apos;s north shore before climbing into marshland around Senjōgahara. The final approach to Yudaki follows a stairway alongside the roaring drop, rewarding hikers with mist-filled viewpoints and the option to continue on to Lake Yunoko.</p>

